    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Here are some red flags for spear-phishing emails that may not rely on obvious malicious links or attachments, focusing on social engineering tactics: \n\n* Overly personalized greetings or references to sensitive information, suggesting the sender has access to sensitive data. \n* Urgency or threats of consequences for not responding quickly, using phrases like \"urgent,\" \"action required,\" or \"your account will be suspended.\" \n* Requests for sensitive information or login credentials, claiming to be from a trusted source or a relevant company department. \n* Unrealistic or flattering language, attempting to build trust or create a sense of obligation. \n* requests to update software or systems with vague, unspecific promises of improvement.",
